annabell
------------------------------------------
ANNABELL is a large-scale cognitive system, entirely based on an artificial
neural network, able to learn complex aspects of natural language starting
from tabula rasa, without any a priori knowledge of the structure of phrases,
meaning of words, role of the different classes of words, only by
communicating with a human through a text-based interface, in a similar way as
humans themselves do.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libgomp1-14.4.0-1
  libgtest0-1.17.0-1bl1
  libpcre1-8.45-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libgtest-devel-1.17.0-1bl1
  libpcre-devel-8.45-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/golosio/annabell

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/golosio/annabell.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack annabell-2.0.9+git20190917-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./annabell-2.0.9+git20190917-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/annabell-2.0.9+git20190917-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/annabell-2.0.9+git20190917-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(annabell)
  /usr/bin/annabell.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/annabell.README
  /usr/share/doc/annabell/AUTHORS
